Contracts Manager - 1854HSI
03 May 2014 09:34 PM - UAE
Job Reference: 1854HSI Contracts Manager - Metro (Greenline) Location: DohaSalary: UAE Dirhams 59000 - UAE Dirhams 64999 per month + Accommodation, Flights, TransportJob Type: PermanentIndustry: Building and ConstructionContracts Manager - Qatar - Metro Project (Greenline)A Contracts Manager is required by leading contracting company within the Middle East for a metro construction scheme in Doha, Qatar.My client specialise in tunnelling, infrastructure works, construction and turnkey contracting. Their project portfolio is extensive and includes large metro schemes, tunnelling works, highways and many other heavy civil contracting projects.The project is part of the prestigious Doha Metro scheme. This particular role will be part of the Greenline project which will link from Msheireb to the Al Rayyan Stadium. It will consist of eight stations and its 16.6km-long twin-bored tunnel will be built at an average of 20 metres. The construction is one of considerable technical difficulty and is one of the largest in the Middle East. The project is part of a joint venture between Porr/Saudi Bin Laden Group/HBK. The project is scheduled to run until 2018.As Contract Manager you will be a suitably qualified and experienced Contract Manager & Claims Expert. An ideal individual is likely to have management experience, and educated to degree level or equivalent, with a proven track record on large-scale projects. You will have ideally worked on tunnelling, metro or rail projects previously with values over $1 Billion USD.The ideal candidate will have:* years experience in Contract Management* 5 years experience working in the Middle East* Degree qualified or equivalent* MRICs* Vast tunnelling or metro experience* Managed a team of Quantity Surveyors & Contracts Administrators previously.The successful candidate will report directly into the Commercial Director and will be working alongside the current Contracts Manager to assist the current requirements and duties on the project. Experience and responsibilities / requirements are likely to include the following:* Contract Administration* Cost Management* Cost Control* Final Accounts* Claims* FIDIC* Subcontracts* Variations* Negotiation* Dispute resolution* Arbitration & (more...)
